'''Fyer''' (also known as '''Fier''') is a [[West Chadic languages|West Chadic]] language spoken in [[Plateau State]], [[Nigeria]].<ref name=e18/>
==Notes== The Fyer tribe has a population of approximately 35,000 people. It is an endangered ethnic group with a declining knowledge of its culture and language.
