{{Infobox language |name = Sanapaná |nativename = ''Sanapana payvoma'' |states = [[Paraguay]] |ethnicity = 2,270 [[Sanapaná people]] (2002 census)<ref name=ISO/> |speakers = {{sigfig|984|2}}<!--E18 mixed up speakers w ethnicity--> |date = 2007 |ref = <ref name=ISO>[http://www-01.sil.org/iso639-3/cr_files/2013-013_spn.pdf ISO change request]</ref> |familycolor = American |fam1 = [[Mascoian languages|Mascoian]] |iso3 = spn |glotto = nucl1655 |glottorefname= Nuclear Sanapana }}
'''Sanapana''' (''sanapana payvoma''<ref>http://www.enlhet.net/pdf/nne28-enlhet-enenlhet.pdf</ref>) is a language of the Paraguayan [[Gran Chaco people|Chaco]]. Use is vigorous, and it is a language of instruction in primary schools.{{fix|text=this may be Angaite, not Sanapana}}.
[[Sanapaná people]] call themselves ''nenlhet'';<ref>http://pueblosoriginarios.com/sur/chaco/sanapana/sanapana.html</ref> [[Enxet people]] call Sanapaná people ''saapa'ang''; [[Indigenous people of Paraguay|Guaná people]] call them ''kasnapan''; and [[Enlhet language|Enlhet people]], ''kelya'mok''.
