In some [[team sport]]s, a '''selector''' is a member of a selection panel which chooses teams or individuals to represent a country or club or other representative team in sporting competitions.

For example, a [[Selector (cricket)|selector in cricket]] is an administrative position involved in choosing players to represent a particular team in a match.<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.sportskeeda.com/cricket/indian-national-selectors-roles-responsibilties | title = Indian National Selectors: Roles and Responsibilities | publisher = Sportskeeda | accessdate = 20 September 2018 }}</ref> Or, in [[Gaelic games]] a selector (sometimes referred to by the [[Irish language|Irish term]] ''roghnóir'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teanglann.ie/en/eid/selector|title=English–Irish Dictionary (de Bhaldraithe): selector|publisher=Teanglann.ie |accessdate = 20 September 2018 }}</ref> is a person who helps pick a team to represent a club or [[Gaelic Athletic Association county|county team]].<ref>{{cite news |title=The man who changed the face of Gaelic football - Independent.ie |url=http://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-football/the-man-who-changed-the-face-of-gaelic-football-29023049.html |publisher =Independent News & Media | date = 18 January 2013 | accessdate = 20 September 2018 }}</ref>

Selectors may be past players,<ref>{{cite web| url = http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/five-selectors-with-13-tests-between-them-bcci-3043120/ | title = Five new India selectors with 13 Tests between them | publisher = Indian Express | accessdate = 20 September 2018 }}</ref> but can also be current coaches. Current captains may also have an influence.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

